This project is licensed under the MIT License (see LICENSE).

It vendors and modifies code from the following upstream project:

  - **doubao-murmur** (https://github.com/yourname/doubao-murmur)
    MIT License, Copyright (c) original authors

All files under `src/doubao_input/doubao/` are derived from the Linux port of
doubao-murmur (`doubao-murmur/linux/`). Each file carries a docstring
attribution to the original Swift source file (e.g., "Mirrors
DoubaoASRClient.swift"). Modifications from the upstream code are:

  1. Internal package imports rewritten from `doubao_murmur.xxx` to
     `doubao_input.doubao.xxx`.
  2. Resource path lookups (`_load_js_resource`) rewritten to read from
     `../login/resources/` instead of `importlib.resources`.
  3. `audio_capture.py`: added an `on_rms` callback hook (int16 RMS
     computed in the audio thread) to drive a real-time waveform in the
     overlay. Upstream only sent raw PCM downstream.
  4. `transcription.py`: added `handle_press()` / `handle_release()`
     methods and a 150 ms debounce (`MIN_PRESS_DURATION`) on top of the
     upstream `handle_toggle()` API, converting the toggle interaction
     into a push-to-hold (push-to-talk) interaction.

Everything else under `src/doubao_input/` (trigger/, inject/, ui/, app.py,
__main__.py) is original work for this project.

Tests under `tests/probe/` are original work.